---
import { HarnessSwapDiagram } from '@metaharness/animations';
import VizPlaceholder from '../../VizPlaceholder.astro';

const capabilities = [
  {
    title: 'Repository knowledge',
    body: [
      'A harness sees one repo at a time. A meta-harness gives the agent a map of the wider system: which repositories exist, how they depend on each other, and where a given concern actually lives.',
      'With that graph in context, the agent can reason across boundaries and go find the right repository to read or work in, instead of assuming everything sits in one tree.',
    ],
    viz: 'repository graph: repos as nodes, dependency edges, one node highlighted in context',
  },
  {
    title: 'Provisioning and setup',
    body: [
      'Knowing about a repository is not the same as being ready to work in it. The meta-harness automates the setup: it provisions the repositories an agent needs, clones them into isolated worktrees, and runs the install and bootstrap scripts.',
      'The manual dance of cloning, branching, and wiring up an environment becomes something that just happens before the agent starts.',
    ],
    viz: 'provisioning: repos clone into worktrees, setup scripts run, environment goes green',
  },
  {
    title: 'Work across repositories at once',
    body: [
      'Awareness is only half of it. A meta-harness lets agents change code across several repositories in one motion: spawning sub-agents to explore or edit each repo in parallel, then opening coordinated PRs so the changes land together instead of breaking each other.',
      'This is what makes the cross-repo reality of modern work ergonomic rather than a manual stitching job.',
    ],
    viz: 'cross-repo change: orchestrator fans out to repos, coordinated PRs open together',
  },
  {
    title: 'Session durability',
    body: [
      'Sessions carry the reasoning behind a change, and today they vanish when the window closes. A meta-harness captures ongoing and finished sessions, stores them outside the context, and indexes them, vector search included, so they stay findable.',
      'Agents can then pull a session back in to resume it, or reference it as prior context for new work, instead of starting cold every time.',
    ],
    viz: 'session capture: sessions stored, indexed, and pulled back into new work',
  },
  {
    title: 'Multiplayer and collaboration',
    body: [
      "Real work in an organization is multiplayer. You do not only build on your own sessions, you extend a coworker's: to debug an issue, to understand the reasoning behind a feature, or to add something on top of it.",
      'Shared, resumable sessions turn individual work into a hive mind, a shared memory the whole organization can draw on.',
    ],
    viz: 'shared sessions across coworkers forming an org-wide knowledge graph',
  },
  {
    title: 'Organizational rules and policies',
    body: [
      'Some concerns belong to the organization, not the individual run. A meta-harness enforces policy at its own layer, checking and verifying the prompts, tools, and actions agents use against the rules your organization sets.',
      'Guardrails live in one place and apply to every harness underneath, in code rather than in a prompt each agent might ignore.',
    ],
    viz: 'policy layer inspecting prompts and actions against org rules',
  },
  {
    title: 'Feedback loops',
    body: [
      'Agents do their best work in loops: repeating cycles of act, verify, and correct until a stop condition is met. A meta-harness makes those loops easy to wrap around your harness.',
      'From a single goal-driven run to scheduled and event-driven loops, work keeps moving with less of a human in the moment.',
    ],
    viz: 'feedback loop: act, verify, correct cycling until a stop condition',
  },
];
---

<section id="capabilities" class="px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent">
        Capabilities
      </p>
      <h2
        class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-4xl"
      >
        What a meta-harness does
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        The meta-harness is still a broad, fast-moving idea. There is no single
        fixed definition yet, and
        <strong class="font-semibold text-neutral-50"
          >the exact properties depend on the type of meta-harness and the scope
          it takes on.</strong
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        Right now the term is used in two ways.{' '}
        <strong class="font-semibold text-neutral-50">Harness optimization</strong>
        {' '}is the Stanford Meta-Harness usage: an outer-loop system searches
        over the harness around an LLM, tuning prompts, memory, retrieval,
        context formatting, tools, completion checks, and runtime code.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-neutral-50">Harness orchestration</strong>
        {' '}is the industry usage: a control layer sits above many agent
        harnesses and handles routing, composition, sandboxing, policy,
        observability, and collaboration.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        Here are some of the potential capabilities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 space-y-12">
      <div
        class="grid items-center gap-8 border-t border-neutral-900 pt-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_18rem]"
      >
        <div class="max-w-xl">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50">
            Swappable harnesses
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
            A meta-harness does not replace Claude Code, Codex, or OpenCode. It
            wraps the harness and augments its capabilities.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
            Because that layer stays thin, <strong
              class="font-medium text-neutral-200"
              >the harness underneath becomes swappable</strong
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <HarnessSwapDiagram client:visible style={{ minHeight: '13rem' }} />
      </div>

      {
        capabilities.map((item) => (
          <div class="grid items-center gap-8 border-t border-neutral-900 pt-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_18rem]">
            <div class="max-w-xl">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50">
                {item.title}
              </h3>
              {item.body.map((para) => (
                <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
                  {para}
                </p>
              ))}
            </div>

            <VizPlaceholder label={item.viz} ratio="aspect-square" />
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
